<br>
Im in the same predicament...Oasis just turned too green for my tastes...<br>
<br>
first try: high keep<br>
  was too high for orcs outside, my air pet was basically powerlevelling everyone (although i got super lucky on a roll for a shralok pack :-) . Too low for fighting inside the keep, or so it seemed as i shouted for group for about an hour with no response.<br>
<br>
Next try: Lake Rathetear<br>
  there are a few pretty good isolated aviak guards, but they are highly camped, and you dont need a partner for them so most people wont group. Good money though by 20 the exp is all blue. i left there too.<br>
<br>
Next: the hermit<br>
  this is one boring mofo! he is always lvl 20, drops some cash and fine steel occasionally. do not use an earth pet on him, i prefer fire, some like air or water (theres something about a 20 point damage shield that makes me so happy, and at level 20 the new healing spell fills up more than half of a fire pets hp)<br>
<br>
Next: crag spiders<br>
  pretty good if you can handle your business. theres no zone nearby and the crags (much like the kerra ridge spiders) seem to gang up from miles away. easy kills until you get two of em on ya...died after about 30 of them, then went back to SK<br>
<br>
Current: SK aviak treehouse<br>
  good place to group with a partner. rooks and darters are yellow and blue (im level 21 now). Was with another mage last night, we had the fire air combo going for some pretty smooth sailing.<br>
<br>
Next: Treants, tesch mas gnolls (23 maybe ill go there)<br>
<br>
anyone have any other ideas? im interested in a good dungeon for a level 20...where should i head to? i couldnt make it very far into najena alone, and the zone was empty most times i go there so i gave up on that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kalamos</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(10/19/00 9:50:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Place to hunt at 20</span><hr size=1> If you want a great place to hunt with minimal to no crowding and have your pick of blue, white, and yellow MOBs then pack your bags, and head for the Lake of Ill Omen in Kunark.  If you don't have Kunark .. then buy it.  You'll want it for hunting in later levels anyways.  If you are &quot;good&quot; aligned then take the boat from Butcherblock to Firiona Vie.  Bind there then invis yourself, cross the North bridge and run West along the shore till you hit a river.  Follow that river right on up to the Lake zone.  Make sure you recast invis if it drops .. the Drachnids (spiders with human bodies .. freaky looking) who frequent the area will kill you quickly.  If you are &quot;evil&quot; aligned then take the raft from Oasis to Tim Deep then from there the boat to The Overthere.  Getting to the Lake of Ill Omen is a little trickier, having to cross The Overthere zone into Warsilks Woods then through a series of tunnels.  EQAtlas.com has some nice maps, I suggest you print them if you plan to go this way.<br>
<br>
Once in the Lake of Ill Omen zone, there are many places to set up camp and hunt.  Just be careful of wandering MOBs.  Finding a nice wall edge or a closeby zone (Frontier Mountains is the only close zone to where you'd be hunting) to pull to is a good idea as things tend to wander here alot.  Simply park your pet, run and and find something, and pull it to your pet.  I did 20-24 here and really enjoyed the change of scenery.  SK and the drive up Kentucky Fried Chicken treehouse was just way too crowded for me (although I did go back there in the late 20's to solo Avocets and Tes Mach Gnolls).<br>
<br>
Different varieties of Sarnaks, Goblins, Skeles and Sabertooth Cats will be your prey.  There can be the occasional rare drop off the Sarnaks if yer lucky.  Make sure you con everything before you pull.  This place is not just for soloing either, I joined groups near the Sarnak fortress many times for faster pulling and some good group fun (Mage downtime can get downright boring sometimes).<br>
<br>
Hope this little semi-spoiler helped.<br>
<br>
Kalamos Darksummons<br>
Mage of 31 Seasons<br>
The Seventh Hammer<br>
